      {
        "id": "e5cc7ad0-fd2b-41a2-b11f-002c7bc253a9",
        "score": 0.5985049,
        "text": "The document is a section from the California Independent System Operator Corporation's Fifth Replacement Electronic Tariff. It outlines requirements for resources providing regulation services:\n\n- Resources must achieve specified Ramp Rates (MW/minute) as per their bid.\n- Regulation capacity should not exceed the maximum Ramp Rate times ten minutes.\n- Telemetry to the CAISO Control Center must indicate resource status.\n- Resources must operate fully within the offered Regulation capacity without manual intervention.\n- Ancillary Service Providers must ensure operational CAISO EMS control and SCADA equipment.\n- Regulation capacity must be dispatchable continuously for at least 60 minutes in the Day-Ahead Market and 30 minutes in the Real-Time Market.\n- CAISO will manage energy from resources reaching award capacity and ensure storage resources meet their State of Charge for Ancillary Services.\n- Scheduling Coordinators for Non-Generator Resources may use Regulation Energy Management.\n- CAISO will provide examples in the Business Practice Manual for Day-Ahead and Real-Time Markets.\n\nThe document is dated August 3, 2024, and is from Section 8.",
        "metadata": {
