        "text": "The document is a section from the California Independent System Operator Corporation's Fifth Replacement Electronic Tariff, focusing on Ancillary Service Control and Capability Standards.\n\n1. **Voltage Regulation**: Generating Units must control net reactive power to maintain scheduled voltage, as assigned by the Participating Transmission Operator (TO) or CAISO, without disabling voltage regulation controls unless permitted by CAISO.\n\n2. **Asynchronous Generating Facilities**: These must also comply with reactive power capability requirements per FERC Order No. 827.\n\n3. **Ancillary Service Control Standards**:\n   - **Regulation**: The Area Control Error (ACE) is managed by CAISO's Energy Management System, which adjusts output to maintain balance.\n   - **Spinning and Non-Spinning Reserve**: Resources must respond to Dispatch Instructions within one minute and reach the required operating level within ten minutes.\n   - **Voltage Support**: Generating Units must have automatic voltage regulators to maintain bus voltages within prescribed limits quickly.\n\n4. **Ancillary Service Capability Standards**:\n   - Resources must convert reserved capacity to energy production within ten minutes of a Dispatch Instruction from CAISO. \n\nThe document outlines specific operational standards and response times for maintaining grid stability and reliability.",
